26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_volt_base.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:35 riastradh Exp $");

29#include "priv.h"
30
31#include <subdev/bios.h>
32#include <subdev/bios/vmap.h>
33#include <subdev/bios/volt.h>
34
35int
36nvkm_volt_get(struct nvkm_volt *volt)
37{
38 int ret, i;
39
40 if (volt->func->volt_get)
41 return volt->func->volt_get(volt);
42
43 ret = volt->func->vid_get(volt);
44 if (ret >= 0) {
45 for (i = 0; i < volt->vid_nr; i++) {
46 if (volt->vid[i].vid == ret)
47 return volt->vid[i].uv;
48 }
49 ret = -EINVAL;
50 }
51 return ret;
52}
53
54static int
55nvkm_volt_set(struct nvkm_volt *volt, u32 uv)
56{
57 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &volt->subdev;
58 int i, ret = -EINVAL;
59
60 if (volt->func->volt_set)
61 return volt->func->volt_set(volt, uv);
62
63 for (i = 0; i < volt->vid_nr; i++) {
64 if (volt->vid[i].uv == uv) {
65 ret = volt->func->vid_set(volt, volt->vid[i].vid);
66 nvkm_debug(subdev, "set %duv: %d\n", uv, ret);
67 break;
68 }
69 }
70 return ret;
71}
72
73static int
74nvkm_volt_map(struct nvkm_volt *volt, u8 id)
75{
76 struct nvkm_bios *bios = volt->subdev.device->bios;
77 struct nvbios_vmap_entry info;
78 u8 ver, len;
79 u16 vmap;
80
81 vmap = nvbios_vmap_entry_parse(bios, id, &ver, &len, &info);
82 if (vmap) {
83 if (info.link != 0xff) {
84 int ret = nvkm_volt_map(volt, info.link);
85 if (ret < 0)
86 return ret;
87 info.min += ret;
88 }
89 return info.min;
90 }
91
92 return id ? id * 10000 : -ENODEV;
93}
94
95int
96nvkm_volt_set_id(struct nvkm_volt *volt, u8 id, int condition)
97{
98 int ret;
99
100 if (volt->func->set_id)
101 return volt->func->set_id(volt, id, condition);
102
103 ret = nvkm_volt_map(volt, id);
104 if (ret >= 0) {
105 int prev = nvkm_volt_get(volt);
106 if (!condition || prev < 0 ||
107 (condition < 0 && ret < prev) ||
108 (condition > 0 && ret > prev)) {
109 ret = nvkm_volt_set(volt, ret);
110 } else {
111 ret = 0;
112 }
113 }
114 return ret;
115}
116
117static void
118nvkm_volt_parse_bios(struct nvkm_bios *bios, struct nvkm_volt *volt)
119{
120 struct nvbios_volt_entry ivid;
121 struct nvbios_volt info;
122 u8 ver, hdr, cnt, len;
123 u16 data;
124 int i;
125
126 data = nvbios_volt_parse(bios, &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &info);
127 if (data && info.vidmask && info.base && info.step) {
128 for (i = 0; i < info.vidmask + 1; i++) {
129 if (info.base >= info.min &&
130 info.base <= info.max) {
131 volt->vid[volt->vid_nr].uv = info.base;
132 volt->vid[volt->vid_nr].vid = i;
133 volt->vid_nr++;
134 }
135 info.base += info.step;
136 }
137 volt->vid_mask = info.vidmask;
138 } else if (data && info.vidmask) {
139 for (i = 0; i < cnt; i++) {
140 data = nvbios_volt_entry_parse(bios, i, &ver, &hdr,
141 &ivid);
142 if (data) {
143 volt->vid[volt->vid_nr].uv = ivid.voltage;
144 volt->vid[volt->vid_nr].vid = ivid.vid;
145 volt->vid_nr++;
146 }
147 }
148 volt->vid_mask = info.vidmask;
149 }
150}
151
152static int
153nvkm_volt_init(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
154{
155 struct nvkm_volt *volt = nvkm_volt(subdev);
156 int ret = nvkm_volt_get(volt);
157 if (ret < 0) {
158 if (ret != -ENODEV)
159 nvkm_debug(subdev, "current voltage unknown\n");
160 return 0;
161 }
162 nvkm_debug(subdev, "current voltage: %duv\n", ret);
163 return 0;
164}
165
166static void *
167nvkm_volt_dtor(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
168{
169 return nvkm_volt(subdev);
170}
171
172static const struct nvkm_subdev_func
173nvkm_volt = {
174 .dtor = nvkm_volt_dtor,
175 .init = nvkm_volt_init,
176};
177
178void
179nvkm_volt_ctor(const struct nvkm_volt_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
180 int index, struct nvkm_volt *volt)
181{
182 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
183 int i;
184
185 nvkm_subdev_ctor(&nvkm_volt, device, index, 0, &volt->subdev);
186 volt->func = func;
187
188 /* Assuming the non-bios device should build the voltage table later */
189 if (bios)
190 nvkm_volt_parse_bios(bios, volt);
191
192 if (volt->vid_nr) {
193 for (i = 0; i < volt->vid_nr; i++) {
194 nvkm_debug(&volt->subdev, "VID %02x: %duv\n",
195 volt->vid[i].vid, volt->vid[i].uv);
196 }
197 }
198}
199
200int
201nvkm_volt_new_(const struct nvkm_volt_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
202 int index, struct nvkm_volt **pvolt)
203{
204 if (!(*pvolt = kzalloc(sizeof(**pvolt), GFP_KERNEL)))
205 return -ENOMEM;
206 nvkm_volt_ctor(func, device, index, *pvolt);
207 return 0;
208}
